  [Text] Friends, as we said in the headlines, <ORGANIZATION>OAS</ORGANIZATION> Secretary 
General <PERSON>Joao Baena Soares</PERSON> today reiterated that <LOCATION>Cuba</LOCATION> should 
return to the <ORGANIZATION>OAS</ORGANIZATION>. After the 25th special session [as heard] of 
the continent-wide organization opened, <PERSON>Baena Soares</PERSON> said that 
<LOCATION>Cuba</LOCATION> is a country of the American hemisphere and should for that 
reason be part of the <ORGANIZATION>OAS</ORGANIZATION>. Baena Soares announced that he will 
continue insisting that this matter be again put on the <ORGANIZATION>OAS</ORGANIZATION> 
agenda for analysis. 

